Message:  # Summary

The CWE-555 weakness describes the storage of plaintext passwords in configuration files for J2EE applications. This allows attackers to easily access password-protected resources by reading the configuration file. It is a child of the more general CWE-260 weakness covering storage of passwords in configuration files. The impact is bypassing access controls by obtaining the password. Mitigations include not hardcoding passwords and encrypting them before storage. CWE-555 is part of the OWASP Top Ten 2004 and related to compromised configuration management.

# Summary bullet points

* Describes storage of plaintext passwords in J2EE application configuration files
* Allows attackers to easily access password-protected resources by reading the file
* Child of the more general CWE-260 - Password in Configuration File
* Impact is bypassing access controls by obtaining the password
* Mitigations include not hardcoding passwords and encrypting before storage
* Part of OWASP Top Ten 2004 and related to compromised configuration management

